    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Beethoven&#8217;s Ninth"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Bradley Thachuk, conductor\r\nMarie-Josée Lord, soprano\r\nStephanie Tritchew, mezzo-soprano\r\nMatthew Dalen, tenor\r\nChristopher Dunham, baritone\r\nChorus Niagara, Robert Cooper, artistic director\r\n\r\nRoydon Tse | Vicious Cycle\r\nWagner | Tristan und Isolde: Prelude and “Liebestod”\r\nBeethoven | Symphony No.9, “Choral”\r\n\r\nThe NSO concludes the 2021/2022 season with Beethoven’s 9th Symphony: a triumphant response to the challenging times at hand."
      }
    ],
